  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nUser requested overview of what Manus knows about him. Manus provided complete static profile including identity, vision, thinking mode, AI relationship expectations, and communication preferences. Key limitation identified: no persistent memory between sessions, only static configuration profile loaded per session.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nUser wanted to validate and understand what information Manus has access to about him in the current session context\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nManus displayed complete user profile table including identity, cognitive architect role, yOS work, communication preferences, and system interaction expectations\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [profile_summary] User Profile Display — Structured table showing all available user context data\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Clear profile structure\n- Transparency about memory limitations\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Static profile injection per session\n- No episodic memory between sessions\n\n## Challenges & Blockers\n\n- No persistent memory across sessions\n- Static profile limits adaptive learning\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- How to implement persistent memory system?\n- Should profile be dynamic vs static?\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Consider building external memory protocol\n- Evaluate need for session persistence\n---\nUID: NpGjgCaJAgZ2M6VMaEqoDa | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0104\n"
}